append() --- it adds elements at the end of a list.
extend() ---- it also adds elements at the end of a list.

difference between these two is such:-

append() --- it takes only one argument and when a list or tuple(or a dictionary) is appended, 
             whole list is added as one single element.
extend() --- it takes iterables as argument(multiple arguments) and adds each element of a list or tuple as individual 
             elements separately